reviewText: Just as good as The Three Faces of Eve and Eleanor Powell deserved to be recognized for her amazing performance.
Always a good performance from Eleanor Parker. A bleak drama well performed by all.

Lizzie had a fine cast and dealt with the same issue of multiple personality syndrome highlighted in the Three Faces of Eve, which overshadowed Lizzie. The two stories are very similar. The movie  Lizzie introduced Johnny Mathis to the entertainment world playing a role as a piano player in a bar.
